This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and argument mining. It may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves searching for relevant information from large text corpora. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning models for classification. It may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the development of models for classification. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the social implications of argument mining.
